entries.name: gs1:AI
entries.description: A Data Type that corresponds to GS1 Application Identifiers defined in the GS1 General Specifications

entries.name: gs1:AdditionalProductClassificationDetails
entries.description: A product classification for the product other than the Global Product Classification(GPC brick value).

entries.name: gs1:AdditiveDetails
entries.description: A set of details about one of the additives within the product.

entries.name: gs1:AllergenDetails
entries.description: Details of an allergen for a product.

entries.name: gs1:AuthenticityDetails
entries.description: A set of details about covert or overt security features that may contribute to checking the authenticity of a product or product instance.

entries.name: gs1:AwardPrizeDetails
entries.description: Describes a prize or award won by a product or organization.

entries.name: gs1:Beverage
entries.description: Any potable liquid.

entries.name: gs1:Brand
entries.description: Information on brands and sub-brands for a product.

entries.name: gs1:CertificationDetails
entries.description: Certification issued by a certifying body to a certification subject (Organization, Place, Product).

entries.name: gs1:Clothing
entries.description: A product that is worn on the body.

entries.name: gs1:ColourCodeDetails
entries.description: A set of colour code details (colour code, party controlling the code list) for the product.

entries.name: gs1:CompulsoryAdditionalInformation
entries.description: The group of compulsory information about a product.

entries.name: gs1:ContactPoint
entries.description: Information on an individual or department acting as point of contact for an organiation.

entries.name: gs1:Country
entries.description: Country is a complex data type that indicates a country and a country subdivision.

entries.name: gs1:DietTypeCodeDetails
entries.description: A set of diet type code details (diet type code and diet type sub code) for the product.

entries.name: gs1:Discount
entries.description: Provides information on a discount applicable to an offer for example 2 percent.

entries.name: gs1:FoodAndBeveragePreparationInformation
entries.description: Food and Beverage Preparation Information is a complex data type that indicates a preparation state code and preparation instructions.

entries.name: gs1:FoodBeverageTobaccoIngredientDetails
entries.description: Food Beverage Tobacco Ingredient is a complex data type that includes an ingredient statement and details.

entries.name: gs1:FoodBeverageTobaccoProduct
entries.description: A food, beverage or tobacco product.

entries.name: gs1:Footwear
entries.description: Outerwear that is worn on the feet such as shoes or boots.

entries.name: gs1:FruitsVegetables
entries.description: Contains properties related specifically to fruit and vegetable products.

entries.name: gs1:GeoCoordinates
entries.description: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

entries.name: gs1:GeoShape
entries.description: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

entries.name: gs1:LocationID_Details
entries.description: Government bodies, trade organisations, and other parties issue identifiers that are associated to locations. Linking these identifiers to GLN and one another supports consolidating records, mapping related, collaborative identifiers, enhances search ability and enables more efficient transitions between identifiers.  This class provides a mechanism for connecting and sharing location identifiers.

entries.name: gs1:LocationStatusHistory
entries.description: Over the lifetime of a location, it may go through periods of being active and inactive. gs1:LocationStatusHistory allows changes in status to be communicated in advance and tracked over time.

entries.name: gs1:MeatPoultry
entries.description: Meat and poultry products.

entries.name: gs1:Message
entries.description: Any kind of electronic message for communication of information from one party to one or more other parties.

entries.name: gs1:MilkButterCreamYogurtCheeseEggsSubstitutes
entries.description: Milk butter cream yogurts cheese eggs and any substitutes for these products.

entries.name: gs1:NutritionMeasurementType
entries.description: A class providing nutritional value and intake percent.

entries.name: gs1:Offer
entries.description: An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service,for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

entries.name: gs1:OrganicClaimDetails
entries.description: A set of organic claim details for the product.

entries.name: gs1:Organization
entries.description: An Organization is any legal or physical entity involved at any point in any supply chain and upon which there is a need to retrieve predefined information. An Organization is uniquely identified by a Global Location Number (GLN).

entries.name: gs1:OrganizationID_Details
entries.description: Government bodies, trade organisations, and other parties issue identifiers that are associated to legal entities and/or functions. Linking these identifiers to GLN and one another supports consolidating records, mapping related, collaborative identifiers, enhances search ability and enables more efficient transitions between identifiers.  This class provides a mechanism for connecting and sharing party identifiers.

entries.name: gs1:OrganizationStatusHistory
entries.description: Over the lifetime of an organisation, it may go through periods of being active and inactive. gs1:OrganizationStatusHistory allows changes in status to be communicated in advance and tracked over time.

entries.name: gs1:PackagingDetails
entries.description: Details on packaging for a product for example packaging type (bottle), materials, features, recycling, etc..

entries.name: gs1:PackagingMaterialDetails
entries.description: Information on any material used for packaging.

entries.name: gs1:Place
entries.description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical location.

entries.name: gs1:PostalAddress
entries.description: The location at which a particular organization or person may be found or reached.

entries.name: gs1:PriceSpecification
entries.description: A structured value representing a monetary amount, consisting of a value and currency code.

entries.name: gs1:Product
entries.description: Any item (product or service) upon which there is a need to retrieve pre-defined information and that may be priced, or ordered, or invoiced at any point in any supply chain.

entries.name: gs1:ProductYieldDetails
entries.description: A grouping of properties related to the yield of a food or beverage product according to a specified type of preparation.

entries.name: gs1:QuantitativeValue
entries.description: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes. A unit of measurement is also specified.

entries.name: gs1:ReferencedFileDetails
entries.description: Provides URL and other information on a referenced electronic file.

entries.name: gs1:RegulatoryIdentifier
entries.description: A repeatable grouping of identifiers that reference one document, record or dataset within one regulatory information system, repository or registry

entries.name: gs1:RegulatoryInformation
entries.description: Information on applicable government regulations applicable to a trade item

entries.name: gs1:RegulatoryNotification
entries.description: A notification message about information on applicable government regulations applicable to a trade item

entries.name: gs1:ReturnablePackageDepositDetails
entries.description: Details of the deposit for returnable packaging for a product.

entries.name: gs1:Seafood
entries.description: Seafood Products including fish and shellfish.

entries.name: gs1:SizeCodeDetails
entries.description: A grouping of properties related to the representing the size of a product, by specifying a value from a specified code list.

entries.name: gs1:SizeDetails
entries.description: A grouping of properties related to the size of a wearable product

entries.name: gs1:TargetMarketDetails
entries.description: A set of target market details (product release date and associated countries) for the product.

entries.name: gs1:TextileMaterialDetails
entries.description: Details on the composition of any materials used to make a product using textiles.

entries.name: gs1:Transaction
entries.description: A repeatable grouping of identifiers that identify a business transaction ID and its type

entries.name: gs1:TypeCode
entries.description: A code list.

entries.name: gs1:WarrantyPromise
entries.description: An assurance that the product is reliable and that repairs or replacement will be done free of charge within a given time limit and under certain conditions in the event of a defect.

entries.name: gs1:WearableProduct
entries.description: Products that are worn on the body.

entries.name: gs1:acceptedPaymentMethod
entries.description: Code indicating a means of payment, for example, BANK_CHEQUE, CASH, etc.

entries.name: gs1:activityIdeas
entries.description: A link to ideas for using a product or engaging in other forms of entertainment, particularly with children.

entries.name: gs1:additionalLocationID
entries.description: Location identifiers assigned and managed by government bodies, trade organisations, and other entities.

entries.name: gs1:additionalOrganizationID
entries.description: Party/organisation identifiers assigned and managed by government bodies, trade organisations, and other entities.

entries.name: gs1:additionalOrganizationIdentificationTypeValue
entries.description: The value associated with the Additional Organization Identification Type Value.

entries.name: gs1:additionalProductClassification
entries.description: Relates to a set of additional product classification details

entries.name: gs1:additionalProductClassificationCode
entries.description: Code specifying the applied additional product classification scheme.

entries.name: gs1:additionalProductClassificationCodeDescription
entries.description: A description related to  the additional product classification code value.

entries.name: gs1:additionalProductClassificationValue
entries.description: Code specifying an additional product classification other than the GS1 Global Product Classification. The applied classification scheme is specified as additional information together with the classification value.

entries.name: gs1:additionalProductDescription
entries.description: Additional variants necessary to communicate to the industry to help define the product. Multiple variants can be established for each GTIN for e.g. Style, Colour, and Fragrance .

entries.name: gs1:additive
entries.description: Relates to details about any additives that a product may contain.

entries.name: gs1:additiveLevelOfContainment
entries.description: Code indicating the level of presence of the additive.

entries.name: gs1:additiveName
entries.description: The name of any additive or genetic modification contained or not contained in the product .

entries.name: gs1:address
entries.description: The postal address for an organization or place.

entries.name: gs1:addressCountry
entries.description: Code specifying the country (and country subdivision) for the address using ISO 3166-1.

entries.name: gs1:addressLocality
entries.description: Text specifying the name of the locality, for example a city.

entries.name: gs1:addressRegion
entries.description: Text specifying a province or state in abbreviated format for example NJ.

entries.name: gs1:addressSuburb
entries.description: A suburb within a town or city.

entries.name: gs1:affiliatedTo
entries.description: Method for associating an organisation/party affiliated to the identified organisation e.g., when engaged in an agent relationship (insurance, shipping, etc).

entries.name: gs1:afterHoursContact
entries.description: Links to after-hours contact information. For general contact details, gs1:contactPoint SHALL be used.

entries.name: gs1:alcoholicBeverageSubregion
entries.description: A legally defined geographical region where the grapes for a wine were grown also known as an appellation. It is recommended to populate this property with an ISO 3166-2 code to indicate country and subdivision.

entries.name: gs1:allergenInfo
entries.description: A link to a description of the allergen information.

entries.name: gs1:allergenLevelOfContainmentCode
entries.description: Code specifying the level of presence of the allergen.

entries.name: gs1:allergenSpecificationAgency
entries.description: The agency or other organization that defines or manages the criteria for allergen containment.

entries.name: gs1:allergenSpecificationName
entries.description: Free text field containing the name and version of the regulation or standard that defines the criteria of allergen containment.

entries.name: gs1:allergenStatement
entries.description: Textual description of the presence or absence of allergens as governed by local rules and regulations, specified as one string.

entries.name: gs1:allergenType
entries.description: Code specifying the type of allergen.

entries.name: gs1:anatomicalForm
entries.description: Describes the meat product in terms of whether it is the whole animal or part of the animal which has been cut such as the muscle, bone, organ, or fat.

entries.name: gs1:appDownload
entries.description: A link to a related mobile app

entries.name: gs1:applicableProducts
entries.description: The set of product identifiers for which this regulatory notification message applies.

entries.name: gs1:applicableTo
entries.description: A property linking a gs1:linkType to the primary GS1 key(s) for which it can be used. Similar to rdfs:Domain but the value space is a GS1 Application Identifier, not a class.

entries.name: gs1:applicableTransactions
entries.description: References one or more business transactions

entries.name: gs1:audioFile
entries.description: Link to a file containing an audio clip which is relevant to the product. Examples are commercials, or instructional/ how to use audio files.

entries.name: gs1:authenticity
entries.description: Links to details of covert/overt security markings that may be used to check authenticity of a product instance.

entries.name: gs1:authenticitySecurityFeatureInstructions
entries.description: Provides human-readable instructions about how to locate a physical security marking and read a value from it.

entries.name: gs1:authenticitySecurityFeatureInstructionsURL
entries.description: Links to online instructions about how to locate a physical security marking and read a value from it.

entries.name: gs1:authenticitySecurityFeatureRegularExpression
entries.description: Links to a regular expression to be used to perform syntax validation (plausibility checking) of a string value read from a physical security marking.

entries.name: gs1:authenticitySecurityFeatureType
entries.description: Links to a URI code value indicating a particular type of physical security marking.

entries.name: gs1:authenticitySecurityFeatureValue
entries.description: Links to a string value read from a physical security marking.

entries.name: gs1:availabilityEnds
entries.description: The date from which the product is no longer available from the information provider, including seasonal or temporary product and services .

entries.name: gs1:availabilityStarts
entries.description: The date from which the product is available from the information provider, including seasonal or temporary product and services.

entries.name: gs1:availableAtOrFrom
entries.description: The location the offered product or service is available from.

entries.name: gs1:availableLanguage
entries.description: ISO 639-1 code specifying the language of a specified contact point.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrize
entries.description: An award or prize given to the product.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrizeCode
entries.description: Indicates the achievement of the product in relation to a prize or award, e.g. winner, runner-up, shortlisted.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrizeCountryCode
entries.description: An ISO standard code identifying the country in which a prize or award is given. It is recommended to populate this property with an ISO 3166-1 country code.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrizeDescription
entries.description: Text that describes the awards won.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrizeJury
entries.description: Free text listing members of the jury that awarded the prize.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrizeName
entries.description: The name of a prize or award which the product has received.

entries.name: gs1:awardPrizeYear
entries.description: The year in which a prize or award was given.

entries.name: gs1:backgroundInfo
entries.description: A link to information typically from the owner of the identified entity about the creative background, thought leadership or influence of the identified entity. This may include the inspiration, innovation for a development process, literary approach or, the science or technology used.

entries.name: gs1:baseLocation
entries.description: A fixed physical location where a mobile location most commonly resides. If gs1:glnType is present, gs1:baseLocationGLN SHALL only be used when gs1:glnType is gs1:GLN_TypeCode-MOBILE_PHYSICAL_LOCATION

entries.name: gs1:bestBeforeDate
entries.description: Best before date on the label or package signifies the end of the period under which the product will retain specific quality attributes or claims even though the product may continue to retain positive quality attributes after this date. Best before date is primarily used for consumer information and may be a regulatory requirement.

entries.name: gs1:beverageVintage
entries.description: The year in which the majority of ingredients are harvested and/or the alcoholic beverage is produced. Determination as to whether the vintage year is the harvest date or production date is according to requirements in the Target Market.

entries.name: gs1:biotinPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Biotin Acid per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:bonelessClaim
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify whether the product makes a specific claim to contain no bones.

entries.name: gs1:brand
entries.description: The brand of the product that appears on the consumer package.

entries.name: gs1:brandHomepageClinical
entries.description: A link to a brand presence aimed at clinical professionals.

entries.name: gs1:brandHomepagePatient
entries.description: A link to a brand presence aimed at patients.

entries.name: gs1:brandName
entries.description: The brand name of the product that appears on the consumer package.

entries.name: gs1:brandOwner
entries.description: The brand owner of the product. The organization that is responsible for allocating the GTIN to the product.

entries.name: gs1:businessEntity
entries.description: Method for noting business structure (e.g., Limited liability company, not for profit).  Expects a repeatable value from gs1:BusinessEntityType code list.

entries.name: gs1:calciumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Calcium per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:carbohydratesPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Carbohydrates per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:careersInfo
entries.description: A link to information about jobs, careers, or other employment opportunities associated to an organisation or location.

entries.name: gs1:catchZone
entries.description: Free text field describing the sea zone from which the product was caught in.

entries.name: gs1:certification
entries.description: Certification information about a product, organisation or location.

entries.name: gs1:certificationAgency
entries.description: Name of the organisation issuing the certification standard or other requirement being met .

entries.name: gs1:certificationAgencyURL
entries.description: URL of the organisation issuing the certification standard or other requirement being met. e.g. https://www.msc.org , https://www.fsc.org

entries.name: gs1:certificationAuditDate
entries.description: Date of completion of the auditing needed for certification

entries.name: gs1:certificationEndDate
entries.description: Last date of validity for the certification. (After this date the certification lapses and would need to be renewed/replaced)

entries.name: gs1:certificationIdentification
entries.description: A reference (i.e, to a certificate instance) issued to confirm that a product, party or location has passed certification. e.g. 'XSC-C-12345'

entries.name: gs1:certificationInfo
entries.description: A link to certification information.

entries.name: gs1:certificationStandard
entries.description: Name of the certification standard. Free text. Example: 'Egg classification' .

entries.name: gs1:certificationStartDate
entries.description: First date of validity for the certification

entries.name: gs1:certificationStatement
entries.description: Certification scope statement of the individual certification instance. The same certificationStandard can be issued with different values of certificationStatement in different instances.

entries.name: gs1:certificationStatus
entries.description: Indicates the current status of the certification, e.g. active or inactive.

entries.name: gs1:certificationSubject
entries.description: References the object (e.g. product, asset, container), party or location being certified. If multiple values are specified, the certification details apply to the logical conjunction (AND) of groups of different types, while a logical disjunction (OR) applies within each group of the same type. For example, two sibling organisations O1 and O2 can process products P1 and P2 at locations L1 and L2: meaning that either organisation can process either product at either location (OR); but the certificate holds for the combinations of organisation (either O1 OR O2) AND product (either P1 OR P2) AND location (either L1 OR L2)

entries.name: gs1:certificationType
entries.description: Indicates the type of certification

entries.name: gs1:certificationURI
entries.description: If gs1:certificationURI is present, it should point to data about this individual certificate within a repository maintained by the certification agency.

entries.name: gs1:certificationValue
entries.description: The certification's standard value. Example: '4'.

entries.name: gs1:cheeseFirmness
entries.description: The firmness of the cheese product for example EXTRA_HARD.

entries.name: gs1:cheeseMaturationPeriodDescription
entries.description: A descriptive way to specify a date range as some cheeses are matured over a period of time, but not an exact period. For example 3 to 4 weeks, over 1 year etc. The term maturation is also known in other markets as Aged.

entries.name: gs1:chloridePerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Chloride per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:cholesterolPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Cholesterol per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:chromiumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Chromium per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:circle
entries.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centred at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

entries.name: gs1:clothingCut
entries.description: Supplemental information to indicate the clothing cut or silhouette make of the garment. For example, silhouette details for a pair of jeans such as boot cut, or loose fit, comfort fit.

entries.name: gs1:collarType
entries.description: A free text description of the type of collar on the garment.

entries.name: gs1:colourCode
entries.description: Relates to a set of details about the colour code for a product

entries.name: gs1:colourCodeList
entries.description: The parties controlling the colour code lists. Dependent on colour code value.

entries.name: gs1:colourCodeValue
entries.description: A code indicating the colour of an object according to a specific code list. The applied code list is specified as additional information together with the colour code.

entries.name: gs1:colourDescription
entries.description: A description of the colour of an object.

entries.name: gs1:companyFilingURL
entries.description: A URI value linking to information related to organisation filing details.

entries.name: gs1:compulsoryAdditionalInformation
entries.description: The legally required/compulsory additional label information as stated on the product packaging or label.

entries.name: gs1:compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformation
entries.description: The legally required/compulsory additional label information as stated on the product packaging or label.

entries.name: gs1:compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformationType
entries.description: The code indicating the type of the legally required/compulsory additional information that is stated on the product packaging label.

entries.name: gs1:consumerFirstAvailabilityDateTime
entries.description: The first date/time that the buyer is allowed to sell the product to consumers. Usually related to a specific geography. ISO 8601 date format CCYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.

entries.name: gs1:consumerHandlingStorage
entries.description: Link to a website, file, or image containing the manufacturer's recommendations for how the consumer or end user should store and handle the product.

entries.name: gs1:consumerHandlingStorageInfo
entries.description: A link to information about safe handling and storage for consumer use.

entries.name: gs1:consumerLifestage
entries.description: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the period or stage in the consumer's life during which the product is considered to be suitable.

entries.name: gs1:consumerPackageDisclaimer
entries.description: Additional information that should be used in advertising and in displaying.

entries.name: gs1:consumerProductVariant
entries.description: The consumer product variant may be used to distinguish one variant of a retail consumer trade item from another if the change does not require the allocation of a different Global Trade Item Number (per the GTIN Management Standard), but communication between trading partners is required to support consumers. The brand owner is responsible for assigning the consumer product variant.

entries.name: gs1:consumerRecyclingInstructions
entries.description: Expresses in text the consumer recycling instructions which are normally held on the label or accompanying the product. Instructions may refer to the 'how' the consumer is supposed to sort the product and packaging materials for recycling.

entries.name: gs1:consumerSafetyInformation
entries.description: Information on consumer safety regarding the product.

entries.name: gs1:consumerSalesCondition
entries.description: A code indicating restrictions imposed on the product regarding how it can be sold to the consumer for example Prescription Required.

entries.name: gs1:consumerStorageInstructions
entries.description: Expresses in text the consumer storage instructions of a product which are normally held on the label or accompanying the product. This information may or may not be labelled on the pack.

entries.name: gs1:consumerUsageInstructions
entries.description: Free text containing the usage instructions of a product, which are normally held on the label or accompanying the product. This information may or may not be labelled on the pack.

entries.name: gs1:contactPoint
entries.description: Contact information. To specify a contact specifically designated for after-hours support, see gs1:afterHoursContact

entries.name: gs1:contactRoleCode
entries.description: The function or role of a contact. Value from gs1:ContactRoleType code list.

entries.name: gs1:contactTitle
entries.description: The job title of the person that can be contacted for example Manager.

entries.name: gs1:contactType
entries.description: The function or role of a contact for example Customer Support.

entries.name: gs1:containedInPlace
entries.description: Designates the larger physical location a sub-location is located within. To specify sub-locations of a physical location, see gs1:containsPlace.

entries.name: gs1:containsPlace
entries.description: Designates a sub-location (e.g., floor, room, shelf) within the physical location being identified. There may be multiple sub-locations associated to a single, physical location. To specify the larger physical location the sub-location is located within, see gs1:containedInPlace

entries.name: gs1:convenienceLevelPercent
entries.description: An indication of the ease of preparation for semi-prepared products. The convenience level indicates the level of preparation in percentage required to prepare and helps the consumer to assess how long it will take to prepare the meal.

entries.name: gs1:coordinateReferenceSystem
entries.description: Open standard spatial reference systems or coordinate reference systems that provide coordinate-based local, regional or global system used to locate geographical entities.  Values should be URIs already defined by the IOPG Geomatics Committee (https://epsg.org/), such as https://epsg.io/4326 (WGS84); https://epsg.io/4267 (NAD27); https://epsg.io/4230 (ED50); https://epsg.io/4618 (SAD69); https://epsg.io/4269 (NAD83).  For elevation values, gs1:elevation SHALL be used.

entries.name: gs1:copperPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Copper per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:countryCode
entries.description: Code specifying the country for the address using ISO 3166-1.

entries.name: gs1:countryOfAssembly
entries.description: The place where product is assembled.

entries.name: gs1:countryOfLastProcessing
entries.description: The place where the product or ingredient was last processed and tested before importation.

entries.name: gs1:countryOfOrigin
entries.description: Code indicating the country of origin of the product.

entries.name: gs1:countryOfOriginStatement
entries.description: A description of the geographic area the item may have originated from or has been processed.

entries.name: gs1:countrySubdivisionCode
entries.description: A short text string code (see values defined in ISO 3166_2) specifying the country subdivision in which an activity is performed, for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

entries.name: gs1:countyCode
entries.description: A code that identifies a county. A county is a territorial division in some countries, forming the chief unit of local administration. In the US, a county is a political and administrative division of a state.

entries.name: gs1:crossStreet
entries.description: A street intersecting a main street (usually at right angles) and continuing on both sides of it.

entries.name: gs1:csrAffiliation
entries.description: A URI value linking to information related to social responsibility activities and associations that an organisation/party is involved with.

entries.name: gs1:customerSupportCentre
entries.description: The organization which provides product support to the trading partner organization to which merchandise is sold.

entries.name: gs1:dailyValueIntakePercent
entries.description: The percentage of the recommended daily intake of a nutrient as recommended by authorities of the target market. Is expressed relative to the serving size and base daily value intake.

entries.name: gs1:defaultLink
entries.description: The default link for a given identified item to which a resolver will redirect unless there is information in the request that is a better match.

entries.name: gs1:defaultLinkMulti
entries.description: A set of 'default links' that may be differentiated by information in the HTTP request headers sent to a resolver to enable a better match than the single default link.

entries.name: gs1:department
entries.description: The name of a division of an organization dealing with a specific activity

entries.name: gs1:dependentProprietaryProduct
entries.description: Dependent products are products which are required to make the current product functional.

entries.name: gs1:descriptiveSize
entries.description: An alphanumeric size factor the brand owner wishes to communicate to the consumer. IE Jumbo, Capri, Full Length, Maxi.

entries.name: gs1:dietCode
entries.description: Links to multiple pairs of gs1:DietTypeCode and diet type sub code (free-form text string).

entries.name: gs1:dietType
entries.description: Code indicating the diet the product is suitable for example Kosher.

entries.name: gs1:dietTypeDescription
entries.description: Free text for indication of diet not stated in the list of diets.

entries.name: gs1:dietTypeSubcode
entries.description: Indicates a set of agreements or a certificate name that guarantees the product is permitted in a particular diet. A diet type subcode is a subclassification of a specific diet type. For example, Pareve is a diet type subcode of Kosher.

entries.name: gs1:digitalAddress
entries.description: The location reference associated to a digital place. If gs1:glnType is present, SHALL only be associated if the value of gs1:glnType is gs1:GLN_TypeCode-DIGITAL_LOCATION.

entries.name: gs1:digitalLocationName
entries.description: The name of a digital place. To specify the name of a physical location, see gs1:physicalLocationName.

entries.name: gs1:discountRepeatsPerMultipleMinimum
entries.description: If specified and set to true, the discount is available for each time the minimum qualifying criteria are met.  This can be used to express '$10 off each $50 spend', which is distinct from a 20% discount because it is quantized in units of spending.

entries.name: gs1:discountType
entries.description: A code that specifies the type of payment discount applicable to an offer, for example BOGO.

entries.name: gs1:dpp
entries.description: A link to a digital product passport.

entries.name: gs1:drainedWeight
entries.description: The weight of the product when drained of its liquid. For example 225 GRM, Jar of pickles in vinegar.

entries.name: gs1:dueDate
entries.description: The date by which an invoice should be paid. This data element represents an attribute of a payment slip reference number, AI (8020), and a Global Location Number (GLN) of the invoicing party.

entries.name: gs1:durationOfWarranty
entries.description: The time period that the warranty is valid within.

entries.name: gs1:dutyFeeTaxAmount
entries.description: The current tax or duty or fee amount applicable to the product, expressed as a floating-point numeric value that is qualified by the corresponding currency. See also gs1:priceCurrency.

entries.name: gs1:dutyFeeTaxDescription
entries.description: A description of tax type for example Taxes sure les supports audio.

entries.name: gs1:dutyFeeTaxRate
entries.description: The current tax or duty rate percentage applicable to the product.

entries.name: gs1:eifu
entries.description: A link to electronic Instruction For Use instructions for Medical Devices.

entries.name: gs1:elevation
entries.description: The elevation of a location (WGS 84). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNITOFMEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone SHALL be a value in meters.

entries.name: gs1:eligibleQuantity
entries.description: The quantity including unit of measure for which the offer for good or service is valid.  If this is not specified, an eligible quantity of 1 should be assumed.

entries.name: gs1:eligibleQuantityMaximum
entries.description: The maximum quantity including unit of measure for which the offer for good or service is valid.

entries.name: gs1:eligibleQuantityMinimum
entries.description: The minimum quantity including unit of measure for which the offer for good or service is valid.

entries.name: gs1:eligibleTradeChannel
entries.description: A code determining the location where a user can redeem the offer, for example ONLINE_ONLY.

entries.name: gs1:email
entries.description: Creating/sending/receiving of unstructured free text messages or documents using computer network, a mini-computer or an attached modem and regular telephone line or other electronic transmission media.

entries.name: gs1:energyFromFatPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Energy from Fat per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:energyPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Energy Per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:epcis
entries.description: A link to an EPCIS repository of visibility event data.

entries.name: gs1:epil
entries.description: A link to an electronic patient information leaflet.

entries.name: gs1:equivalentProduct
entries.description: A product which can be substituted for the product based on supplier-defined functional equivalence to the product.

entries.name: gs1:eventsInfo
entries.description: A link to event details.  For a page specifically for scheduling a reservation or booking an appointment, see gs1:scheduleTime.

entries.name: gs1:exactDiscountAmount
entries.description: Links to a gs1:PriceSpecification that indicates in terms of an amount and specified currency, the exact discount on the sales price associated with a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express '$10 off'.

entries.name: gs1:exactDiscountPercentage
entries.description: A floating-point value indicating an exact percentage discount on the sales price associated with a particular gs1:Discount.  This property can be used to express '15% discount'.

entries.name: gs1:exclusionDescription
entries.description: A text description of any products, brands, or categories that cannot be used with the offer

entries.name: gs1:expirationDate
entries.description: The expiration date is the date that determines the limit of consumption or use of a product/coupon. Its meaning is determined based on the trade item context (e.g., for food, the date will indicate the possibility of a direct health risk resulting from use of the product after the date, for pharmaceutical products, it will indicate the possibility of an indirect health risk resulting from the ineffectiveness of the product after the date). It is often referred to as 'use by date' or 'maximum durability date'.

entries.name: gs1:expirationDateTime
entries.description: The manufacturer determines the expiration date and time, which is relevant only for short duration and for items that will not be sent on long distances and not outside of the time zone. A typical application of AI (7003) is in hospitals or public pharmacies for special, customised, products which may have a 'life duration' shorter than one single day. The life duration varies according the pharmaceutical substances used in the treatment. The precise expiration date and time is defined at the end of the manufacturing process, and can be barcoded on the product label as an attribute to the item's GTIN. Where there is no business requirement to express the expiration date to the nearest hour (or less), AI (17) Expiration date should be used.

entries.name: gs1:faqs
entries.description: A link to a set of frequently asked questions.

entries.name: gs1:fatInMilkContent
entries.description: The percentage of fat contained in milk content of the product.

entries.name: gs1:fatPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Fat per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:fatpercentageInDryMatter
entries.description: The amount of fat contained in the base product expressed in percentage.

entries.name: gs1:faxNumber
entries.description: A fax number used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media.

entries.name: gs1:fibrePerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Fibre per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:fileLanguageCode
entries.description: The specified language to which the digital asset is targeted. It is recommended to use the ISO 639-1 language code.

entries.name: gs1:filePixelHeight
entries.description: The number of pixels along the vertical axis of the image.

entries.name: gs1:filePixelWidth
entries.description: The number of pixels along the horizontal axis of the image.

entries.name: gs1:firstFreezeDate
entries.description: The first freeze date is applicable to products that are frozen directly after slaughtering, harvesting, catching or after initial processing of the product. Examples include fresh meat, meat products or fishery products. The first freeze date is determined by the organisation conducting the freezing.

entries.name: gs1:fishType
entries.description: The type of fish for example Sea bass.

entries.name: gs1:fluoridePerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Fluoride per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:folicAcidPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Folic Acid per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:foodBeverageRefrigerationClaim
entries.description: Identifies whether or not the product requires refrigeration.

entries.name: gs1:foodBeverageTargetUse
entries.description: The type of meal the food or beverage product is targeted to for example Breakfast.

entries.name: gs1:footwearFasteningType
entries.description: Something that mechanically joins or affixes two or more parts together in a footwear product for example a shoe lace.

entries.name: gs1:footwearUpperType
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify whether the footwear upper is open or closed. Otherwise known as Open or Closed Upper.

entries.name: gs1:franchiseeOf
entries.description: Method for associating the franchisor organisation to the franchisee.

entries.name: gs1:franchisorOf
entries.description: Method for associating franchisee organisation(s) to the franchisor.

entries.name: gs1:freshOrSeawaterFarmed
entries.description: A code determining whether the fish originated from the sea or was farmed.

entries.name: gs1:functionalName
entries.description: Describes use of the product or service by the consumer. Should help clarify the product classification associated with the GTIN.

entries.name: gs1:geneticallyModifiedDeclaration
entries.description: A statement of the presence or absence of genetically modified protein or DNA.

entries.name: gs1:geo
entries.description: Links to information about geocoordinates or geoshapes for a place.

entries.name: gs1:glnType
entries.description: Indicates what type of thing is being identified by a GLN.

entries.name: gs1:globalLocationNumber
entries.description: A Global Location Number (GLN) is the GS1 Identification Key used to identify physical locations or parties. The key comprises a GS1 Company Prefix, Location Reference and Check Digit. For more information see https://www.gs1.org/gln.

entries.name: gs1:gpcCategoryCode
entries.description: 8-digit code (GPC Brick Value) specifying a product category according to the GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) standard. For more information see https://www.gs1.org/gpc

entries.name: gs1:gpcCategoryDescription
entries.description: A description of the code specifying a product category according to the GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) standard.

entries.name: gs1:grossArea
entries.description: The overall area of the item including packaging. This can be given using a number of different AI ranges that depend on the units in which the area is measured.

entries.name: gs1:grossVolume
entries.description: The overall volume of the item including packaging. This can be given using a number of different AI ranges that depend on the units in which the volume is measured.

entries.name: gs1:grossWeight
entries.description: Used to identify the gross weight of the product. The gross weight includes all packaging materials of the product. At pallet level the productGrossWeight includes the weight of the pallet itself. For example, 200 GRM, value - total pounds, total grams, etc.

entries.name: gs1:growingMethod
entries.description: The process through which fresh produce is grown and cultivated.

entries.name: gs1:gtin
entries.description: A Global Trade Item Number (GTIN) is the 14 digit GS1 Identification Key used to identify products. The key comprises a GS1 Company Prefix followed by an Item Reference Number and a Check Digit. See https://www.gs1.org/gtin  for more details.

entries.name: gs1:handledBy
entries.description: Used when one resolver redirects all request URIs that match a given pattern without further processing, such as from GS1 to a brand-operated service. See section 7.7.1 of the Digital Link standard, version 1.1.

entries.name: gs1:harvestDate
entries.description: The harvest date. For example, the harvest date can be the date when an animal was slaughtered or killed, a fish has been harvested, or a crop was harvested. This date  is determined by the organisation conducting the harvesting. Different organisations may use more specific terminology when referring to their specific needs and use terms such as: Date of catch or slaughter date.

entries.name: gs1:harvestDateEnd
entries.description: The harvest end date. For example, the harvest end date can be the date when an animal was slaughtered or killed, a fish has been harvested, or a crop was harvested. This end date is determined by the organisation conducting the harvesting. Different organisations may use more specific terminology when referring to their specific needs and use terms such as: Date of catch or slaughter date. When referring to animals the date range refers to the whole animal and all meat or fish cuts derived from this animal.

entries.name: gs1:harvestDateStart
entries.description: The harvest start date. For example, the harvest start date can be the date when an animal was slaughtered or killed, a fish has been harvested, or a crop was harvested. This start date is determined by the organisation conducting the harvesting. Different organisations may use more specific terminology when referring to their specific needs and use terms such as: Date of catch or slaughter date. When referring to animals the date range refers to the whole animal and all meat or fish cuts derived from this animal.

entries.name: gs1:hasAllergen
entries.description: Relates to details about allergens

entries.name: gs1:hasBatchLotNumber
entries.description: The batch or lot number associates an item with information the manufacturer considers relevant for traceability of the trade item to which the element string is applied. The data may refer to the trade item itself or to items contained. The number may be, for example, a production lot number, a shift number, a machine number, a time, or an internal production code. In cases where the same product is manufactured in different locations the brand owner and the manufacturer are responsible for ensuring the non-duplication of batch/lot numbers for a GTIN. For the re-use of batch/lot numbers with a GTIN, sector-specific constraints need to be considered.

entries.name: gs1:hasPrimaryLocation
entries.description: Links to the place(s) that this organisation designates as their primary location(s).

entries.name: gs1:hasRetailers
entries.description: A link to a list of retailers.

entries.name: gs1:hasReturnablePackageDeposit
entries.description: links to details of amounts refunded for returnable package in a specified region.

entries.name: gs1:hasSerialNumber
entries.description: A serial number is assigned to an entity for its lifetime. When combined with a GTIN, a serial number uniquely identifies an individual item. The serial number field is alphanumeric and may include all characters contained in figure 7.11-1. The brand owner and the manufacturer are responsible for ensuring the non-duplication of serial numbers for a GTIN. For the re-use of serial numbers with a GTIN, sector-specific constraints need to be considered.

entries.name: gs1:hasThirdPartyControlledSerialNumber
entries.description: This identifier is assigned to an entity for its lifetime. When combined with a GTIN, a TPX uniquely identifies an individual item and forms a unit pack Unique Identifier (upUI) for tobacco traceability per EU 2018/574. The serial number field is alphanumeric and may include all characters contained in figure 7.11-1. The Third Party determines the TPX, but the TPX shall begin with the ID Issuer Unique Identification Code (UIC), followed by GS1 UIC Extension 1, and GS1 UIC Extension 2.

entries.name: gs1:healthClaimDescription
entries.description: A description of health claims according to regulations of the target market.

entries.name: gs1:homepage
entries.description: A link to general information about an organisation or brand. Typically the homepage of an organisation's website. It may include links to further information such as certifications, careers, payments, reservations, etc.

entries.name: gs1:image
entries.description: Link to a file containing a visual representation of the product.

entries.name: gs1:inPackageDepth
entries.description: The depth of the product in its packaging, as measured according to the GS1 Package Measurement Rules. See https://www.gs1.org/package-measurement-rules-implementation-guide for more details.

entries.name: gs1:inPackageDiameter
entries.description: The measurement of the diameter of the product in its package at its largest point. For example, 165 MMT.

entries.name: gs1:inPackageHeight
entries.description: The height of the product in the package, as measured according to the GS1 Package Measurement Rules. See https://www.gs1.org/package-measurement-rules-implementation-guide for more details.

entries.name: gs1:inPackageWidth
entries.description: The width of the product in the package, as measured according to the GS1 Package Measurement Rules. See https://www.gs1.org/package-measurement-rules-implementation-guide for more details.

entries.name: gs1:includedAccessories
entries.description: Any included object or device not part of the core product itself but which adds to its functionality or use.

entries.name: gs1:ingredient
entries.description: Links to information about ingredients of a specific Food/Beverage/Tobacco product.

entries.name: gs1:ingredientContentPercentage
entries.description: Quantity of the ingredient contained in the product as a percentage of the total product ingredients. This is used in conjunction with ingredientName.

entries.name: gs1:ingredientName
entries.description: Free text field describing an ingredient or ingredient group. Ingredients include any additives (colourings, preservatives, e-numbers, etc.) that are encompassed.

entries.name: gs1:ingredientOfConcern
entries.description: Indicates a claim to an ingredient, considered to be a concern for regulatory or other reasons, and which is 'contained' within the product but may not need to specify the amount whether approximate, or an accurate measurement be given.

entries.name: gs1:ingredientSequence
entries.description: Integer (1, 2, 3...) indicating the ingredient order by content percentage of the product. (major ingredient = 1, second ingredient = 2) etc.

entries.name: gs1:ingredientStatement
entries.description: Information on the constituent ingredient make up of the product specified as one string.

entries.name: gs1:ingredientsInfo
entries.description: A link to facts about ingredients.

entries.name: gs1:initialCertificationDate
entries.description: The date when the certification was originally issued. May differ from the certificationStartDate of the current recertification cycle.

entries.name: gs1:instructions
entries.description: A link to instructions, such as assembly instructions, usage tips etc.  It is not appropriate to use this link type for healthcare regulated content applications for which specific link types are available.

entries.name: gs1:instructionsForUse
entries.description: Link to a file containing the Instructions For Use.

entries.name: gs1:iodinePerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Iodine per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:ironPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Iron per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:irradiatedCode
entries.description: Indicates if radiation has been applied to the product.

entries.name: gs1:isCarbonated
entries.description: Used to identify whether or not a beverage product is naturally effervescent or has been made effervescent by the addition of carbon dioxide gas.

entries.name: gs1:isDecaffeinated
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify whether or not the product contains caffeine.

entries.name: gs1:isFromConcentrate
entries.description: Used to identify whether or not the product claims to be made from a concentrated formulation.

entries.name: gs1:isHomogenised
entries.description: A The indication whether or not the milk used was actively homogenised. The homogenisation of milk is a technical process in the dairy. The milk fat is milled to such an extent that further creaming is prevented.

entries.name: gs1:isInstant
entries.description: Determines whether the product is instant.

entries.name: gs1:isMaternity
entries.description: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify if the product is intended as maternity wear.

entries.name: gs1:isOnlyAvailableThroughRetailer
entries.description: If specified and set to true, the discount is only available through the retailer making the offer.

entries.name: gs1:isOnlyWithMailingListSignup
entries.description: If specified and set to true, the discount is only available for customers who have signed up to the retailer's mailing list.

entries.name: gs1:isOnlyWithPaymentCard
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing using one of the specified payment card types.

entries.name: gs1:isOnlyWithRetailerLoyaltyCard
entries.description: If specified and set to true, the discount is only available for holders of the retailer's own loyalty card.

entries.name: gs1:isOnlyWithRetailerPaymentCard
entries.description: If specified and set to true, the discount is only available for holders of the retailer's own store payment card.

entries.name: gs1:isPatterned
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify whether or not the product has a patterned design.

entries.name: gs1:isPittedStoned
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify whether or not a fruit or vegetable product has been de-stoned or pitted prior to being offered for sale.

entries.name: gs1:isProductRecalled
entries.description: An indicator for the product to determine if the Manufacturer or Supplier has recalled the product.

entries.name: gs1:isPromoterExclusiveOffer
entries.description: Determines whether the offer is only provided by the promoter

entries.name: gs1:isRindEdible
entries.description: An indicator whether or not the cheese rind is edible. Some cheeses are coated in plastic or their surface is treated with other traditional substances to increase their shelf life. This can result in the rind no longer being edible.

entries.name: gs1:isSeedless
entries.description: Determines whether the product is seedless as grown.

entries.name: gs1:isShelledPeeled
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify whether or not the product or its contents have been shelled/peeled prior to being offered for sale.

entries.name: gs1:isSliced
entries.description: Determines whether the product comes pre-sliced.

entries.name: gs1:isThermal
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used to identify whether the product is thermal.

entries.name: gs1:isVintage
entries.description: Identifies whether the product makes claim to being vintage.

entries.name: gs1:isWashedReadyToEat
entries.description: Determines whether product has been prewashed and is ready to eat.

entries.name: gs1:isWaterproof
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used to identify whether or not the product claims to provide waterproofing to the applied surface.

entries.name: gs1:isWearableItemDisposable
entries.description: Identifies whether or not the product is intended to be disposed of after single use or a limited period of use.

entries.name: gs1:itemOffered
entries.description: The product included in the offer.

entries.name: gs1:juiceContentPercent
entries.description: The fruit juice content of the product expressed as a percentage.

entries.name: gs1:jws
entries.description: A link to a JSON Web Signature

entries.name: gs1:latitude
entries.description: Angular distance North or South from the earth's equator measured through 90 degrees.

entries.name: gs1:leasedFrom
entries.description: Links to the organisation (lessor) from which this place is leased.

entries.name: gs1:leasedTo
entries.description: Links to the organisation(s) (lessee(s)) to which this place is leased. Property SHOULD be applied to a specific sub-location, rather than a main location, wherever possible.

entries.name: gs1:leaveReview
entries.description: A link through which a review can be added.

entries.name: gs1:lesseeOf
entries.description: Links to the place(s) for which this organisation is the lessee (i.e., this organisation leases those places from another organisation, the lessor).

entries.name: gs1:lessorFor
entries.description: Links to the place(s) for which this organisation is the lessor (i.e., this organisation leases those places to others).

entries.name: gs1:line
entries.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more point objects separated by a space. A single line segment (i.e., straight line) is expressed as two points.  A multi-line path (i.e., open polygon) is expressed as a series of three or more points. For a closed shape, gs1:polygon SHALL be used.

entries.name: gs1:linkType
entries.description: Provides a URL for related information or services. This is not expected to be used directly but provides a super property for all other link types in the GS1 ecosystem.

entries.name: gs1:location
entries.description: The place(s) associated with an organization.

entries.name: gs1:locationDescription
entries.description: The description of a place.

entries.name: gs1:locationFinalClosureDate
entries.description: Date in which a location was finally closed. Note that this is NOT the date when a GLN was deactivated. To designate when location opened, see gs1:locationOpeningDate.

entries.name: gs1:locationGLN
entries.description: 13-digit GLN that is being used to identify a physical or digital location. If gs1:glnType is present, gs1:locationGLN SHALL only be used when gs1:GLN_TypeCode includes FIXED_PHYSICAL_LOCATION, MOBILE_PHYSICAL_LOCATION, or DIGITAL_LOCATION

entries.name: gs1:locationHistory
entries.description: Provides details on if and when a location is active or inactive.

entries.name: gs1:locationID
entries.description: Identifier value associated to a location. This value SHALL follow rules set forth by the administrating organisation designated in gs1:LocationID_Type.

entries.name: gs1:locationID_Qualifier
entries.description: Secondary qualifier to supplement gs1:LocationID_Type meaning. May be used with proprietary ID code values to define identifier administrator.

entries.name: gs1:locationID_Type
entries.description: Organisation that administers the gs1:locationID or the name of the ID itself.  Value from gs1:LocationID_Type code list.

entries.name: gs1:locationID_URI
entries.description: A URI that links to information about the gs1:locationID.

entries.name: gs1:locationInfo
entries.description: A link to a map, directions, or other location-related information.  For B2B location  information, see gs1:logisticsInfo.  For details specific to hours of operation, see gs1:openingHoursInfo

entries.name: gs1:locationOpeningDate
entries.description: Date in which a location was opened or otherwise established. Note that this is NOT the date when a GLN was allocated to identify the location. To designate when location was finally closed, see gs1: gs1:locationFinalClosureDate

entries.name: gs1:locationRole
entries.description: A location classification based on the purpose, type of site and/or what occurs there. Repeatable value from gs1:LocationRoleType code list.

entries.name: gs1:locationStatus
entries.description: Designation of active/inactive status of a location.

entries.name: gs1:logisticsInfo
entries.description: A link to B2B logistics information related to a physical location.

entries.name: gs1:longitude
entries.description: The arc or portion of the earth's equator intersected between the meridian of a given place and the prime meridian and expressed in degrees

entries.name: gs1:loyaltyProgram
entries.description: A link to information about a loyalty program, including a member's current status and/or a registration option for new members

entries.name: gs1:magnesiumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Magnesium per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:makesOffer
entries.description: An offer made by an organization.

entries.name: gs1:managedBy
entries.description: Links to the organisation that manages this place or organisation, as designated by the owner or another organisation.

entries.name: gs1:managedFor
entries.description: Links to the organisation(s) for whom this place is managed. Property SHOULD be applied to a specific sub-location, rather than a main location, wherever possible.

entries.name: gs1:manages
entries.description: Links to the place(s) or organisation(s) that this organisation manages, on behalf of the owner or another organisation.

entries.name: gs1:manganesePerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Manganese per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:manufacturer
entries.description: The organization that produces the item.

entries.name: gs1:manufacturerPreparationCode
entries.description: Code indicating the preparation methods that a manufacturer has used in the manufacturing of a product for example DEEP_FRY.

entries.name: gs1:manufacturersWarranty
entries.description: The warranty associated with the product.

entries.name: gs1:manufacturingPlant
entries.description: A physical location consisting of one or more buildings with facilities for manufacturing.

entries.name: gs1:massPerUnitArea
entries.description: The mass per unit area of the item. This can be given using a number of different AI ranges that depend on the units in which the mass and area are measured.

entries.name: gs1:masterData
entries.description: A link to a source of structured master data for the entity. This is typically for B2B applications.

entries.name: gs1:maturationMethod
entries.description: The method of maturity for the item for example tree ripened or jet fresh.

entries.name: gs1:maxPrice
entries.description: Provides a maximum price value as a floating-point numeric value that is qualified by the corresponding currency. See also gs1:priceCurrency

entries.name: gs1:maximumDiscountAmount
entries.description: Links to a gs1:PriceSpecification that indicates in terms of an amount and specified currency, the maximum discount on the sales price associated with a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express 'up to $10 off'.

entries.name: gs1:maximumDiscountPercentage
entries.description: A floating-point value indicating a maximum percentage discount on the sales price associated with a particular gs1:Discount.  This property can be used to express 'up to 15% discount'.

entries.name: gs1:maximumOptimumConsumptionTemperature
entries.description: The upper limit drinking temperature of the optimum range of the drinking temperature. The optimum range of the drinking temperature is a recommendation and is based on the experience of the individual producer. Allows for the representation of the same value in different units of measure but not multiple values.

entries.name: gs1:maximumQualifyingItems
entries.description: Specifies the maximum number of items that qualify for a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express 'maximum N items per customer'.

entries.name: gs1:maximumQualifyingSpend
entries.description: Links to a gs1:PriceSpecification that indicates in terms of an amount and specified currency, the maximum spend that qualifies for a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express 'for purchases of up to $100'.

entries.name: gs1:meatPoultryType
entries.description: The fish, meat, or poultry type for this food and beverage item.

entries.name: gs1:menuInfo
entries.description: A link to menu details. This may include food menus, services, or other offerings provided by an organisation or at a location.  For details specific to allergens only, see gs1:allergenInfo .  For details specific to nutrition information only, see gs1:nutritionalInfo .  For details specific to ingredients only, see gs1:ingredientsInfo .

entries.name: gs1:messageRecipient
entries.description: Identifies the party receiving an electronic message

entries.name: gs1:messageSender
entries.description: Identifies the party sending an electronic message

entries.name: gs1:minPrice
entries.description: Provides a minimum price value as a floating-point numeric value that is qualified by the corresponding currency. See also gs1:priceCurrency

entries.name: gs1:minimumDiscountAmount
entries.description: Links to a gs1:PriceSpecification that indicates in terms of an amount and specified currency, the minimum discount on the sales price associated with a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express 'at least $10 off'.

entries.name: gs1:minimumDiscountPercentage
entries.description: A floating-point value indicating a minimum percentage discount on the sales price associated with a particular gs1:Discount.  This property can be used to express 'at least 15% discount'.

entries.name: gs1:minimumFishContent
entries.description: The minimum amount of fish contained in a food and beverage product expressed as a measurement.

entries.name: gs1:minimumMeatPoultryContent
entries.description: The minimum amount of fish, meat or poultry contained in a food and beverage product expressed as a measurement.

entries.name: gs1:minimumOptimumConsumptionTemperature
entries.description: The lower limit drinking temperature of the optimum range of the drinking temperature. The optimum range of the drinking temperature is a recommendation and is based on the experience of the individual producer. Allows for the representation of the same value in different units of measure but not multiple values.

entries.name: gs1:minimumQualifyingItems
entries.description: Specifies the minimum number of items that must be purchased to qualify for a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express 'if you buy at least N items'.

entries.name: gs1:minimumQualifyingSpend
entries.description: Links to a gs1:PriceSpecification that indicates in terms of an amount and specified currency, the minimum spend required to qualify for a particular gs1:Discount. This property can be used to express 'if you spend at least $100'.

entries.name: gs1:molybdenumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Molybdenum per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:monounsaturatedFatPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Monounsaturated fat per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:netArea
entries.description: The net area of the item. This can be given using a number of different AI ranges that depend on the units in which the area is measured.

entries.name: gs1:netContent
entries.description: The quantity of the product contained by a package, usually as claimed on the label. Indicates the net content of the total product. For fixed value products use the value claimed on the package, to avoid variable fill rate issue that arises with some product which are sold by volume or weight, and whose actual content may vary slightly from batch to batch.

entries.name: gs1:netWeight
entries.description: Used to identify the net weight of the product. Net Weight excludes all packaging material, including the packaging material of all lower-level GTINs. Example:11.5 kgm.

entries.name: gs1:niacinPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Niacin per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:numberOfServingsPerPackage
entries.description: The total number of servings contained in the package.

entries.name: gs1:numberOfServingsPerPackageMeasurementPrecision
entries.description: Code indicating whether the number of servings per package is exact or approximate.

entries.name: gs1:numberOfServingsRangeDescription
entries.description: A free text field specifying a range for the number of servings contained in the package.

entries.name: gs1:nutrientBasisQuantity
entries.description: Quantity on which the nutrient information has been based; for example, per 100 grams. When specified, nutrientBasisQuantity establishes the basis for all contained nutrient records.

entries.name: gs1:nutrientBasisQuantityType
entries.description: The type of quantity specified in the nutrientBasisQuantity for example measurement, serving size, or container. This is used in conjunction with the nutrientBasisQuantity.

entries.name: gs1:nutrientMeasurementPrecision
entries.description: The Code indicating whether the specified nutrient content is exact or approximate.

entries.name: gs1:nutritionalClaim
entries.description: Code indicating a nutritional claim applicable to the product, for example FAT_FREE.

entries.name: gs1:nutritionalClaimStatement
entries.description: Free text field for any additional nutritional claims.

entries.name: gs1:nutritionalInfo
entries.description: A link to nutritional facts.

entries.name: gs1:occupiedBy
entries.description: Links to the organisation(s) that occupy this place. Property SHOULD be applied to a specific sub-location, rather than a main location, wherever possible.

entries.name: gs1:occupies
entries.description: Links to the place(s) that this organisation occupies.

entries.name: gs1:offerDescription
entries.description: A description of the offer including goods or services offered for sale or use.

entries.name: gs1:offerDiscount
entries.description: A discount associated with an offer.

entries.name: gs1:offerRedemptionType
entries.description: A code indicating the type of redemptions that apply to the offer, for example single use.

entries.name: gs1:offerRedemptionURL
entries.description: The URL where the offer seeker will need to go in order to redeem the offer for an online redemption.

entries.name: gs1:offerRestrictionDescription
entries.description: A description of what the offer is restricted to, relative to all other offerings by the issuer, for example payment restrictions, subscription required, new customers only.

entries.name: gs1:openingHoursInfo
entries.description: A link to details on hours of operation.

entries.name: gs1:organicClaim
entries.description: Relates to an organic claim about the product

entries.name: gs1:organicClaimAgency
entries.description: A governing body that creates and maintains standards related to organic products.

entries.name: gs1:organicPercentClaim
entries.description: The percent of actual organic materials per weight of the product. This is usually claimed on the product.

entries.name: gs1:organizationFormationDate
entries.description: Date in which an organisation was formed or otherwise established. Note that this is NOT the date when a GLN was allocated to identify the organisation. To designate when organisation was terminated, see gs1:organizationTerminationDate

entries.name: gs1:organizationHistory
entries.description: Provides details on if and when an organisation/party is active or inactive.

entries.name: gs1:organizationID
entries.description: Identifier value associated to an organisation/party. This value SHALL follow rules set forth by the administrating organisation designated in gs1:OrganizationID_Type.

entries.name: gs1:organizationID_Qualifier
entries.description: Secondary qualifier to supplement gs1:organizationID_Type meaning. May be used with proprietary ID code values to define identifier administrator.

entries.name: gs1:organizationID_Type
entries.description: Organisation that administers the gs1:organizationID or the name of the ID itself.  Value from gs1:OrganizationID_Type code list.

entries.name: gs1:organizationID_URI
entries.description: A URI that links to information about the gs1:organizationID.

entries.name: gs1:organizationLegalName
entries.description: The legal name used by an organisation for official purposes. There may be more than one legal name, particularly in countries with more than one official language. In such cases the language of the string should be identified. To specify a general name, see gs1:organizationName. For trade name, see gs1:organizationTradingName. To specify the name of a function, see gs1:department.

entries.name: gs1:organizationName
entries.description: The name of the organization expressed in text.

entries.name: gs1:organizationRole
entries.description: The role and/or purpose of a party (i.e. legal entity or function).  Multiple values from gs1:OrganizationRoleType code list may be associated to a single organisation/party.

entries.name: gs1:organizationStatus
entries.description: Designation of active/inactive status of an organisation/party.

entries.name: gs1:organizationTerminationDate
entries.description: Date in which an organisation was disbanded or otherwise ended. Note that this is NOT the date when a GLN was deactivated. To designate when organisation formed, see gs1:organizationFormationDate.

entries.name: gs1:organizationTradingName
entries.description: A trading name or alternative forms of a legal entity's name as recognised by some jurisdictions. To specify a general name, see gs1:organizationName. For legal name, see gs1:organizationLegalName. To specify the name of a function, see gs1:department.

entries.name: gs1:originalCodeValue
entries.description: Links to the alphanumeric code value defined elsewhere in GS1 or the GS1 Global Data Dictionary

entries.name: gs1:outOfPackageDepth
entries.description: The depth of the product out of its packaging, as measured according to the GS1 Package Measurement Rules. See https://www.gs1.org/package-measurement-rules-implementation-guide for more details.

entries.name: gs1:outOfPackageDiameter
entries.description: The measurement of the diameter of the product out of its package at its largest point. For example, 165 MMT.

entries.name: gs1:outOfPackageHeight
entries.description: The height of the product out of the package, as measured according to the GS1 Package Measurement Rules. See https://www.gs1.org/package-measurement-rules-implementation-guide for more details.

entries.name: gs1:outOfPackageWidth
entries.description: The width of the product out of the package, as measured according to the GS1 Package Measurement Rules. See https://www.gs1.org/package-measurement-rules-implementation-guide for more details.

entries.name: gs1:ownedBy
entries.description: Links to the organisation(s) that own this place, in full or in part. This includes joint ventures. For leased locations, see gs1:lessorFor and gs1:isLeasedFrom.

entries.name: gs1:owns
entries.description: Links to the place(s) or organisation(s) that this organisation owns.

entries.name: gs1:packaging
entries.description: Details on the packaging for a product including type, weight and materials.

entries.name: gs1:packagingDate
entries.description: The packaging date is the date when the goods were packed as determined by the packager. The date may refer to the trade item itself or to items contained.

entries.name: gs1:packagingFeature
entries.description: Code indicating a feature that facilitates the usage of the product by the consumer, for example a handle. Packaging features do not affect the core composition of the packaging type nor modify its usage.

entries.name: gs1:packagingFunction
entries.description: Code indicating specific functionality for packaging resulting from specific processes or features present in the packaging type,for example, ANTI_TAMPERING.

entries.name: gs1:packagingMarkedDietAllergenType
entries.description: Indication of which dietary or allergen marks are on the package.

entries.name: gs1:packagingMarkedFreeFrom
entries.description: Indication of the food ingredients that the package is marked free from.

entries.name: gs1:packagingMarkedLabelAccreditation
entries.description: A marking that the product received recognition, endorsement, certification by following guidelines by the label issuing agency. This does not represent claims for regulatory purposes on products such as free from markings.

entries.name: gs1:packagingMaterial
entries.description: links to details about packaging material type, quantity and thickness

entries.name: gs1:packagingMaterialCompositionQuantity
entries.description: The quantity of the packaging material of the product. Can be weight, volume or surface, can vary by country.

entries.name: gs1:packagingMaterialThickness
entries.description: The thickness of a packaging material.

entries.name: gs1:packagingMaterialType
entries.description: The materials used for the packaging of the product for example glass or plastic.

entries.name: gs1:packagingRecyclingProcessType
entries.description: The process the packaging could undertake for recyclable & sustainability programs. Examples COMPOSTABLE, ENERGY_RECOVERABLE, REUSABLE.

entries.name: gs1:packagingRecyclingScheme
entries.description: A code indicating the recycling scheme the packaging of this product will fall within when recycled. Applies to recyclable packaging with or without deposit.

entries.name: gs1:packagingShape
entries.description: A code depicting the shape of a package for example CONE.

entries.name: gs1:packagingType
entries.description: The dominant means used to transport, store, handle or display the product as defined by the data source. This packaging is not used to describe any manufacturing process.Recommend to use UNECE Rec 21 codes.

entries.name: gs1:pantothenicAcidPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Pantothenic Acid per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:parentOrganization
entries.description: Designates the legal entity or function directly above the organisation/party being identified in a hierarchy. This is not defaulted to the highest-level entity in the hierarchy. Only one parent organisation SHALL be associated to a single GLN. To specify other affiliated organisations, see gs1:affiliatedTo, gs1:managedBy, gs1:franchiseeOf, gs1:ownedBy. To specify an organisation/party lower in the hierarchy, see gs1:subOrganization.

entries.name: gs1:partyGLN
entries.description: 13-digit GLN that is being used to identify a legal entity or function. If gs1:glnType is present, gs1:partyGLN SHALL only be used when gs1:GLN_TypeCode includes LEGAL_ENTITY and/or FUNCTION

entries.name: gs1:paymentLink
entries.description: A link to a place where payments details are provided and/or payments can be made by the user.
