entries.name: gs1:paymentTerms
entries.description: The type of payment term expressed as a code, for example Discount.

entries.name: gs1:percentageOfAlcoholByVolume
entries.description: The percentage of alcohol contained in product.

entries.name: gs1:phosphorusPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Phosphorus per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:physicalLocationName
entries.description: The name of a physical place. To specify the name of a digital location, see gs1:digitalLocationName.

entries.name: gs1:pip
entries.description: A link to information specifically about the identified item, typically operated by the brand owner or a retailer of the product and aimed at consumers. It may include links to further information, product description, specifications etc.

entries.name: gs1:polygon
entries.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

entries.name: gs1:polyolsPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Polyols per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:polyunsaturatedFatPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Polyunsaturated fat per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:postOfficeBoxNumber
entries.description: The number that identifies a PO box. A PO box is a box in a post office or other postal service location assigned to an organization where postal items may be kept.

entries.name: gs1:postalCode
entries.description: Text specifying the postal code for an address.

entries.name: gs1:postalName
entries.description: The name of the recipient expressed in text. Note that this may be different than gs1:OrganizationName.

entries.name: gs1:potassiumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Potassium per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:preparationCode
entries.description: Code specifying the preparation state of the product for which the nutrient information is valid. PREPARED, UNPREPARED.

entries.name: gs1:preparationConsumptionPrecautions
entries.description: Specifies additional precautions to be taken before preparation or consumption of the product.

entries.name: gs1:preparationInformation
entries.description: Links to information about how to prepare a specific Food/Beverage/Tobacco product.

entries.name: gs1:preparationInstructions
entries.description: Free text providing instructions on how to prepare the product before serving.

entries.name: gs1:preservationTechnique
entries.description: Code indicating the preservation technique used to preserve the product from deterioration, for example, BRINING.

entries.name: gs1:price
entries.description: Provides a price value as a floating-point numeric value that is qualified by the corresponding currency. See also gs1:priceCurrency. The price value indicates the unit price unless the property gs1:eligibleQuantity is specified and indicates multiple units

entries.name: gs1:priceCurrency
entries.description: A string value indicating a currency from ISO 4217 for example USD .

entries.name: gs1:priceSpecification
entries.description: The price related to an offer. If the offer is a multi-buy offer for a quantity of product greater than one unit, this should be indicated using the property gs1:eligibleQuantity

entries.name: gs1:primaryAlternateProduct
entries.description: A product that is similar to the current product but is not exact match. Same form fit function, e.g. same product different colour, different package size, better quality.

entries.name: gs1:primaryLocationOf
entries.description: Links to the organisation(s) that designate this place as its/their primary location. Property SHOULD be applied to a specific sub-location, rather than a main location, wherever possible.

entries.name: gs1:productDescription
entries.description: An understandable and useable description of a product using brand and other descriptors. This attribute is filled with as little abbreviation as possible, while keeping to a reasonable length.  This should be a meaningful description of the product with full spelling to facilitate message processing. Retailers can use this description as the base to fully understand the brand, flavour, scent etc. of the specific product, in order to accurately create a product description as needed for their internal systems. Examples: XYZ Brand Base Invisible Solid Deodorant AP Stick Spring Breeze.

entries.name: gs1:productFeatureBenefit
entries.description: Element for consumer facing marketing content to describe the key features or benefits of the style suitable for display purposes.

entries.name: gs1:productFormDescription
entries.description: The physical form or shape of the product. Used, for example, in pharmaceutical industry to indicate the formulation of the product. Defines the form the product takes and is distinct from the form of the packaging.

entries.name: gs1:productID
entries.description: Additional means to the Global Trade Item Number to identify a product.

entries.name: gs1:productMarketingMessage
entries.description: Marketing message associated with the product. Consumer-friendly marketing detailed description of the product.

entries.name: gs1:productName
entries.description: Consumer friendly short description of the product suitable for compact presentation.

entries.name: gs1:productRange
entries.description: A name, used by a Brand Owner, that span multiple consumer categories or uses. E.g. (Waist Watchers).

entries.name: gs1:productSustainabilityInfo
entries.description: This term has been deprecated. Please use gs1:sustainabilityInfo instead.

entries.name: gs1:productYield
entries.description: Product quantity after preparation. This can differ based on productYieldType

entries.name: gs1:productYieldType
entries.description: Code indicating the type of yield measurement specified in productYield. Examples: AFTER_DILUTION, DRAINED_WEIGHT.

entries.name: gs1:productYieldVariationPercentage
entries.description: Indication of range in percent of the given cooking / roasting loss. Percentage that the actual weight of the product differs upward or downward from the average or estimated product yield.

entries.name: gs1:productionDate
entries.description: The production date is the production or assembly date determined by the manufacturer. The date may refer to the trade item itself or to items contained.

entries.name: gs1:productionDateTime
entries.description: The date and time of production (or assembly). The date and time of production is determined by the manufacturer. The date and time may refer to the trade item itself or to the items contained.

entries.name: gs1:productionVariantDescription
entries.description: Free text assigned by the manufacturer to describe the production variant. Examples are: package series X, package series Y.

entries.name: gs1:productionVariantEffectiveDateTime
entries.description: The start date of a production variant. The variant applies to products having a date mark (a best before date or expiration date) on the package that comes on or after the effective date.

entries.name: gs1:promotion
entries.description: A link to a promotion.

entries.name: gs1:proteinPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Protein per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:provenanceStatement
entries.description: Free text description of the region or place the product originates from. This is to be specifically used to specify areas such as cities, mountain ranges, regions. Examples: Made in the Thuringen Mountains, Made in Paris, From the Napa Valley.

entries.name: gs1:purchaseSuppliesOrAccessories
entries.description: A link to information about where supplies or accessories for the item can be purchased or ordered.

entries.name: gs1:qualifyingBrandName
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing a product from one of the brand names specified via this property.

entries.name: gs1:qualifyingGPCs
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing a product whose Global Product Classification (GPC) brick value appears in the list specified via this property.

entries.name: gs1:qualifyingProductCategoryDescription
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing a product from categories specified in this free-form text field.

entries.name: gs1:qualifyingProductClassificationCode
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing a product whose product classification (other than GPC) appears in the list specified via this property. This property specifies a product classification other than GPC.

entries.name: gs1:qualifyingProductGTINs
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing a product whose GTIN appears in the list specified via this property.

entries.name: gs1:qualifyingSubBrandName
entries.description: If specified, the discount is only available when purchasing a product from one of the sub-brand names (specified product ranges for a given brand) specified via this property.

entries.name: gs1:quickStartGuide
entries.description: A link to a description of the key features needed to be understood to begin using the item or interacting with something new.

entries.name: gs1:recallStatus
entries.description: A link to information about whether the product has been recalled or not, typically an API.

entries.name: gs1:recipeInfo
entries.description: A link to a recipe website.

entries.name: gs1:referencedFile
entries.description: Link to a file or website containing additional information on product.

entries.name: gs1:referencedFileEffectiveEndDateTime
entries.description: The date upon which the target of this external link ceases to be effective for use.

entries.name: gs1:referencedFileEffectiveStartDateTime
entries.description: The date upon which the target of this external link begins to be effective for use.

entries.name: gs1:referencedFileSize
entries.description: The size of the file as it is stored in an uncompressed format.

entries.name: gs1:referencedFileType
entries.description: A code indicating the purpose or role of file (not a MIME type) that is being referenced, for example PRODUCT_LABEL_IMAGE. This code is used when the purpose of a file is not specified in the property.

entries.name: gs1:referencedFileURL
entries.description: Simple text string that refers to a resource on the internet, URLs may refer to documents, resources, people, etc.

entries.name: gs1:registerProduct
entries.description: A link to an entry point for registering ownership of a product including for warranty purposes.

entries.name: gs1:registryEntry
entries.description: A link to an entry in a register, such as a business register or register of locations. Such registers may act as alternative identifiers, such as official company numbers, LEIs, other location identifiers etc.

entries.name: gs1:regulatedProductName
entries.description: The prescribed, regulated or generic product name or denomination that describes the true nature of the product. For example for a food product in order to distinguish it from other foods according to country specific regulations.

entries.name: gs1:regulationType
entries.description: Links to a code indicating the type of government regulation.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryAct
entries.description: The name given to the requirement assigned by the regulatory agency.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryIdentifier
entries.description: Links to one or more groupings of identifiers that reference documents or datasets within a regulatory information system, repository or registry.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryIdentifierType
entries.description: The code indicating the type of regulatory information that is referenced.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryInformation
entries.description: Links to one or more groupings of information on applicable government regulations applicable to a trade item.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryInformationProvider
entries.description: The organisation that provided a document or dataset to a regulatory information system, repository or registry.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryReferenceApplicabilityEndDate
entries.description: The final date for which the referenced information remains applicable.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryReferenceApplicabilityStartDate
entries.description: The earliest date from which the referenced information becomes applicable.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryReferenceNumber
entries.description: A reference number for a record, document or dataset stored within a regulatory information system, repository or registry.

entries.name: gs1:regulatoryVerificationNumber
entries.description: A verification number for a record, document or dataset stored within a regulatory information system, repository or registry, typically used in combination with the reference number when requesting access to the refrenced document or dataset.

entries.name: gs1:reheatingClaim
entries.description: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging whether a food product which is ready to eat can be reheated if required prior to consumption.

entries.name: gs1:relatedImage
entries.description: A link to any image that depicts or relates to the identified entity (e.g., trade item, assets, business process, patient record, location, organisation, etc.)

entries.name: gs1:relatedOrganization
entries.description: The organisation(s) associated with a place.

entries.name: gs1:relatedVideo
entries.description: A link to any video, or document that has an embedded video, that describes or relates to the identified item, organisation, or location in some way.

entries.name: gs1:replacedByOrganization
entries.description: Links to the successor organisation that is used in place of a previous organisation

entries.name: gs1:replacedByPlace
entries.description: Links to the successor location that is used in place of a previous location

entries.name: gs1:replacedByProduct
entries.description: The product which permanently replaces the current product. This product is sent in the record for the original item that is being replaced.

entries.name: gs1:replacedOrganization
entries.description: Links to the previous organisation that this organisation replaces

entries.name: gs1:replacedPlace
entries.description: Links to the previous location that this location replaces

entries.name: gs1:replacedProduct
entries.description: Indicates the product identification of an item that is being permanently replaced by this product.

entries.name: gs1:reportFound
entries.description: A link to a platform or service where users (company or a person) can report a found item associated with the identified entity (instance of an item). This link type is designed to assist in connecting the found item with its rightful owner or relevant authorities.

entries.name: gs1:responsibility
entries.description: Text further specifying the area of responsibility of the trade contact.

entries.name: gs1:responsibleForLocation
entries.description: Links to the place(s) for which this organisation is responsible.

entries.name: gs1:responsibleOrganization
entries.description: Links to the organisation that is directly responsible for this place.

entries.name: gs1:returnablePackageDepositAmount
entries.description: The monetary amount for the individual returnable package.

entries.name: gs1:returnablePackageDepositRegion
entries.description: The geographic region associated with the returnable package deposit amount.

entries.name: gs1:review
entries.description: A link to reviews.

entries.name: gs1:riboflavinPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Riboflavin per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:safetyInfo
entries.description: A link to safety information.

entries.name: gs1:saltPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Salt per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:saturatedFatPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Saturated fat per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:scheduleTime
entries.description: A link to a site that offers information on scheduling, appointments, or reservations. This may or may not allow the user to book the reservation.

entries.name: gs1:seasonCalendarYear
entries.description: The calendar year in which the product is seasonally available.

entries.name: gs1:seasonName
entries.description: Element defines the season applicable to the item for example Winter.

entries.name: gs1:seasonParameter
entries.description: Code indicating the season in which the product is available, e.g. SPRING, WINTER

entries.name: gs1:seeker
entries.description: The organization seeking an offer.

entries.name: gs1:selectedProductsOnly
entries.description: If specified and set to true, the discount only applies to specific products selected by the retailer or offer promoter - not to all items in that product category.  This property should be asserted and set to true for offers that say 'on selected products'.

entries.name: gs1:seleniumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Selenium per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:sellByDate
entries.description: The date specified by the manufacturer as the last date the retailer is to offer the product for sale to the consumer. The product should not be merchandised after this date.

entries.name: gs1:seller
entries.description: The organization seeking to sell a product or service.

entries.name: gs1:serviceInfo
entries.description: A link to service or maintenance instructions.

entries.name: gs1:servingSize
entries.description: Measurement value specifying the serving size in which the information per nutrient has been stated. Example: Per 100 GRM.

entries.name: gs1:servingSizeDescription
entries.description: A free text field specifying the serving size for which the nutrient information has been stated for example: per 1/3 cup (42 g).

entries.name: gs1:servingSuggestion
entries.description: Free text field for serving suggestion.

entries.name: gs1:sharpnessOfCheese
entries.description: The descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the sharpness of the taste of the product for example EXTRA_SHARP. Usually the longer the aging of the product, the sharper the taste.

entries.name: gs1:siteAccessRequirements
entries.description: A URI value linking to information related to requirements for accessing or visiting a place.

entries.name: gs1:size
entries.description: Links a wearable product to one or more groupings of gs1:SizeDetails representing size systems, size groups, size type and size dimensions.

entries.name: gs1:sizeCode
entries.description: Links a product to one or more groupings of gs1:SizeCodeDetails representing the size value from a specified code list.

entries.name: gs1:sizeCodeListCode
entries.description: Code specifying a size code list. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List SizeCodeListCode .

entries.name: gs1:sizeCodeValue
entries.description: A code indicating the size of an object according to a specific code list. The applied code list is specified as additional information together with the size code.

entries.name: gs1:sizeDimension
entries.description: The numerical size measurement relating to the size type.

entries.name: gs1:sizeGroup
entries.description: Code indicating the type of size that is necessary to uniquely specify the size of the item, for example, BOYS.

entries.name: gs1:sizeSystem
entries.description: The system that is being used to define the size for example EUROPE. Size system is used in conjunction with size group to define the size dimension.

entries.name: gs1:sizeType
entries.description: The type of size dimension being specified for example SLEEVE.

entries.name: gs1:smartLabel
entries.description: A link to the product's SmartLabel page.

entries.name: gs1:smpc
entries.description: A link to Summary Product Characteristics. To be used specifically when linking to information for healthcare professionals.

entries.name: gs1:socialMedia
entries.description: A link to a social media channel. The title will typically be replaced by the name of the channel.

entries.name: gs1:sodiumPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Sodium per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:sourceAnimal
entries.description: Code indicating the source of raw material used to produce the food product, for example a GOAT for milk.

entries.name: gs1:sportingActivityType
entries.description: Code indicating the type of sporting activity for which the product is intended to be worn, for example FOOTBALL.

entries.name: gs1:starchPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Starch per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:statisticInfo
entries.description: A link to information about statistics regarding an organisation, location, or other entity.

entries.name: gs1:statusTimestamp
entries.description: Date and time (including optional timezone) associated to status designations. Timestamps may be future dated to provide advance notice of status changes. For further information about the required lexical representation of date, time, and timezone please see https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#dateTime

entries.name: gs1:streetAddress
entries.description: The street address expressed as free form text. The street address is printed on paper as the first lines below the name. For example, the name of the street and the number in the street or the name of a building. A total of four street address lines are available. gs1:streetAddress SHOULD be used before populating lines two through four. For a PO Box gs1:postOfficeBoxNumber SHOULD be used instead.

entries.name: gs1:streetAddressLine2
entries.description: The second line of the street address, expressed as free form text. The street address is printed on paper as the first lines below the name. For example, the name of the street and the number in the street or the name of a building. A total of four street address lines are available. gs1:streetAddress SHOULD be used before populating lines two through four. These SHALL NOT be used as alternatives to the dedicated address properties gs1:addressSuburb, gs1:addressLocality and gs1:addressRegion.

entries.name: gs1:streetAddressLine3
entries.description: The third line of the street address, expressed as free form text. The street address is printed on paper as the first lines below the name. For example, the name of the street and the number in the street or the name of a building. A total of four street address lines are available. gs1:streetAddress and gs1:streetaddressLine2 SHOULD be used before populating lines three and four. These SHALL NOT be used as alternatives to the dedicated address properties gs1:addressSuburb, gs1:addressLocality and gs1:addressRegion.

entries.name: gs1:streetAddressLine4
entries.description: The fourth line of the street address, expressed as free form text. The street address is printed on paper as the first lines below the name. For example, the name of the street and the number in the street or the name of a building. gs1:streetAddress, gs1:streetaddressLine2 and gs1:streetaddressLine3 SHOULD be used before populating line four. These SHALL NOT be used as alternatives to the dedicated address properties gs1:addressSuburb, gs1:addressLocality and gs1:addressRegion.

entries.name: gs1:styleDescription
entries.description: An attribute that classifies products that share many of the same characteristics (attribute values) that does NOT vary by GTIN, and are presented by the supplier as a single merchandise selection for the buyer.

entries.name: gs1:subBrandName
entries.description: Second level of brand. Can be a trademark. It is the primary differentiating factor that a brand owner wants to communicate to the consumer or buyer. E.g. Yummy-Cola Classic. In this example Yummy-Cola is the brand and Classic is the sub-brand.

entries.name: gs1:subOrganization
entries.description: Designates a legal entity or function directly below the organisation/party being identified in a hierarchy. There may be multiple sub-organisations associated to a single GLN. To specify other affiliated organisations, see gs1:manages, gs1:franchisorOf, gs1:owns. To specify a parent organisation, see gs1:parentOrganization.

entries.name: gs1:subscribe
entries.description: A link to a subscription form

entries.name: gs1:sugarsPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Sugars per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:supplierSpecifiedMinimumConsumerStorageDays
entries.description: Represents the number of days between a product's sell by date and its use by date.

entries.name: gs1:support
entries.description: A link to a source of support such as a helpdesk, chat support, email etc.

entries.name: gs1:sustainabilityInfo
entries.description: A link to information relating to sustainability and recycling requirements or processes.

entries.name: gs1:sweetnessLevelOfAlcoholicBeverage
entries.description: Indicates the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the sweetness of the alcoholic beverage. These are sometimes placed on a label. In some markets, the term is based on the amount of sugar content according to local regulation.

entries.name: gs1:targetConsumerAge
entries.description: Identifies the target consumer age range for which a product has been designed.

entries.name: gs1:targetConsumerGender
entries.description: Identifies the target consumer gender for which a product has been designed for example MALE

entries.name: gs1:targetMarket
entries.description: Relates to a set of target market details (product release date and associated countries)

entries.name: gs1:targetMarketCountries
entries.description: List of countries representing the target market for a particular release date indicated by gs1:consumerFirstAvailabilityDateTime

entries.name: gs1:telephone
entries.description: A telephone number for example +44 217 992 9999.

entries.name: gs1:textileMaterial
entries.description: One or more links to information about the materials used in a wearable product.

entries.name: gs1:textileMaterialContent
entries.description: A description of the material composition used in conjunction with the material percentage.

entries.name: gs1:textileMaterialDescription
entries.description: This provides a name or brief description of one material contained within the product, for example Rayon.

entries.name: gs1:textileMaterialPercentage
entries.description: Corresponding net weight percentage of the product material specified via gs1:textileMaterialDescription, e.g. 70.

entries.name: gs1:textileMaterialThreadCount
entries.description: The quality of material (fabric) of a product based on the total number of vertical and horizontal threads in one square inch.

entries.name: gs1:textileMaterialWeight
entries.description: The measured weight of the material expressed in ounces per square yard or grams per square meter.

entries.name: gs1:thiaminPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Thiamin per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:traceability
entries.description: A link to traceability information (includes track and trace).  Traceability information may be provided for consumption by humans or computers. If the target is an EPCIS repository, use gs1:epcis instead.

entries.name: gs1:transFatPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Trans Fat per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:transactionDate
entries.description: The date associated with a business transaction

entries.name: gs1:transactionID
entries.description: An identifier for a business transactions

entries.name: gs1:transactionType
entries.description: The code indicating the type of business transactions

entries.name: gs1:tutorial
entries.description: A link to a tutorial or set of tutorials, such as online classes, how-to videos etc.

entries.name: gs1:unitCode
entries.description: A string value indicating a Measurement Unit from UN/ECE Recommendation 20, Units of Measure used in International Trade e.g. GRM = gram - see http://www.unece.org/fileadmin/DAM/cefact/recommendations/rec20/rec20_rev3_Annex3e.pdf

entries.name: gs1:upperMaterialType
entries.description: The material(s) used for the upper part of the footwear product. The upper is the part of a shoe, boot, slipper or other item of footwear that is above the sole.

entries.name: gs1:userAgreement
entries.description: A link to an agreement or waiver.

entries.name: gs1:usesManagedLocation
entries.description: Links to the place(s) that this organisation uses as a managed space.

entries.name: gs1:validFrom
entries.description: The effective start date of the price .

entries.name: gs1:validThrough
entries.description: The effective end date of the price .

entries.name: gs1:value
entries.description: A floating-point numeric value that is qualified by the corresponding measurement unit code - see gs1:unitCode

entries.name: gs1:variantDescription
entries.description: Free text field used to identify the variant of the product. Variants are the distinguishing characteristics that differentiate products with the same brand and size including such things as the particular flavour, fragrance, taste.

entries.name: gs1:verificationService
entries.description: A link to a GS1 Lightweight Messaging Service for verifying the status of a product, organisation, or location and its identifier.

entries.name: gs1:vintner
entries.description: The person hired by a winery or wine company who is responsible for many of the processes in the preparation, taste and quality of the wine produced. The science of wine making is referred to as oenology. The vintner is the oenologist.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminAPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin A per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminB12PerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin B12 per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminB6PerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin B6 per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminCPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin C per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminDPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin D per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminEPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin E per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:vitaminKPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Vitamin K per specified nutrient basis quantity.

entries.name: gs1:warningCopyDescription
entries.description: Warning information is additional information that outlines special requirements, warning and caution information printed on the package.

entries.name: gs1:warranty
entries.description: The warranty associated with the product, as provided by the manufacturer.

entries.name: gs1:warrantyScopeDescription
entries.description: The description of warranty available for the product. Allows for the representation of the same value in different languages but not for multiple values.

entries.name: gs1:whatsInTheBox
entries.description: A link to a description of all the individual items in a packaged item.

entries.name: gs1:yield
entries.description: Product quantity after preparation.

entries.name: gs1:zincPerNutrientBasis
entries.description: Zinc per specified nutrient basis quantity.
